<HEADLINE> Piazza Homers, Ties Club Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Mike Piazza tied a New York Mets club record  
for the second time this season when he homered in his fourth 
straight game Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza drove a 2-2 pitch from San Diego's Sterling Hitchcock an  
estimated 448 feet into the second deck at Qualcomm Stadium to give 
the Mets a 1-0 lead in the second inning. It was his 27th this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the seventh time a Mets player accomplished the feat.  
Piazza also homered in four straight games from May 17-21. 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza's shot was the 24th to reach the second deck in 31  
seasons. He became the first opponent to hit two loge launches. The 
first was Sept. 22, 1996, when he was with the Los Angeles Dodgers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
