<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 15:00:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Escapes Spur Pa. Prison Lockdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARRISBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Gov. Tom Ridge on Monday ordered a  
lockdown of all state prisons following the escape of two inmates 
from a facility in eastern Pennsylvania that came two weeks after a 
murderer broke out of another institution. 
</P>
<P>
	Corrections officials would not immediately say how Michael  
McCloskey, 43, and Anthony Yang, 31, escaped the medium-security 
State Correctional Institution at Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
	McCloskey, who was serving a life sentence for murder, and Yang,  
who was serving a 20- to 50-year sentence for arson, were 
discovered missing about 10:45 a.m. Monday. The two shared a cell. 
</P>
<P>
	The escapes came as authorities continue to search for Norman  
Johnston, a four-time killer who broke out of the maximum-security 
State Correctional Institution at Huntingdon on Aug. 2 after 
cutting his way through a cell window and two security fences. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is unacceptable,'' Ridge said. ``I have ordered the  
immediate lockdown of the entire state prison system, and I have 
directed Secretary (Martin) Horn to begin an immediate check of 
every security system at every one of our 24 institutions.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ridge also directed State Police Commissioner Paul Evanko to  
begin round-the-clock patrols on the perimeter of state prisons. 
</P>
<P>
	While authorities focused their search efforts Monday for  
McCloskey and Yang near the prison 100 miles northwest of 
Philadelphia, police have been searching for Johnston in 
southeastern Pennsylvania, Maryland and Delaware. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnston was convicted in March 1980 of killing four teen-agers  
to cover up a multimillion-dollar burglary ring he ran with his two 
brothers. The film ``At Close Range,'' starring Sean Penn, was 
based on the case. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
