<HEADLINE> N.Y. Van Flip Kills 2, Injures 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTLAND, N.Y. (AP) -- A van carrying 15 people home from a  
family reunion flipped and rolled on the New York State Thruway on 
Monday morning, killing two people and throwing 13 others onto the 
roadway and into a field. 
</P>
<P>
	The group had been traveling all night after attending a reunion  
in Greenville, Miss. Two of the van's eight adults, including the 
driver, died following the crash, which occurred about 50 miles 
west of Buffalo. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said the driver, Doris Lewis, 43 -- a Buffalo  
police officer -- apparently dozed off, awoke as the van was leaving 
the road and overcorrected the steering, sending the van into a 
sideways roll. 
</P>
<P>
	Seven children, ages 5 to 13, were among those thrown from the  
van as it rolled at least three times and came to rest against a 
tree. 
</P>
<P>
	``There were people scattered all over, and some were real  
serious and some were very young,'' Capt. David O'Connor said. 
</P>
<P>
	Five of the children were in critical condition, and the others  
were in serious and good condition. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
