<HEADLINE> Red Sox Activate Scott Hatteberg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Boston Red Sox on Monday activated catcher  
Scott Hatteberg from the 15-day disabled list and signed 
first-round draft pick Rick Asadoorian to a minor league contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Hatteberg went on the disabled list on May 17 to recover from  
surgery on his right elbow. He was on a 20-day rehabilitation 
assignment that ended Friday and when the Red Sox delayed restoring 
him to the roster, Hatteberg contemplated filing a grievance. 
</P>
<P>
	But the team designated catcher Lenny Webster for assignment on  
Monday, making room for Hatteberg. 
</P>
<P>
	Asadoorian, a 19-year-old outfielder from Whitinsville, hit .500  
with seven homer and 41 RBIs in his senior year at Northbridge High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
	Asadoorian was the 17th overall selection in the draft. His  
signing bonus is worth $1,825,000, including payments for college 
education, according to The Boston Globe. 
  	   	
</P>
