<HEADLINE> Miami Heat Re-signs Dan Majerle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- The Miami Heat re-signed forward Dan Majerle to a  
one-year contract Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Majerle, who turns 34 next month, started 48 of the Heat's 50  
games last season. He averaged 7.0 points and 4.3 rebounds per 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	The signing reflects coach Pat Riley's desire to keep his team  
intact even though the Heat have lost in the first round of the 
playoffs the past two years. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami's other roster moves this offseason have been the signing  
of free agent forward Otis Thorpe, and the loss of guard Terry 
Porter, who signed a free-agent contract with San Antonio. 
  	   	
</P>
