<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> India Said Can Build Neutron Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- India can build a neutron bomb and  
nuclear weapons of ``any type or size,'' scientists who planned 
last year's nuclear tests said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Rajagopal Chidambaram, chairman of the Atomic Energy Commission,  
said it would not be difficult to build neutron bombs, which 
produce a smaller blast than conventional nuclear weapons but have 
more intense radiation. Neutron bombs limit structural damage while 
killing large numbers of people. 
</P>
<P>
	Anil Kakodkar, director of the Bhabha Atomic Research Center,  
said India had declared a moratorium on nuclear tests after its 
five underground explosions in May 1998, but had not stopped its 
nuclear weapons research. 
</P>
<P>
	``The research is on. We have not stopped,'' Kakodkar was quoted  
as saying by Press Trust of India. He gave no details. 
</P>
<P>
	India says it needs a minimum nuclear deterrent to arm itself  
against possible attacks by its neighbors, Pakistan to the west and 
China to the north. 
</P>
<P>
	Amid U.S. charges of atomic spying, China declared last month it  
possessed its own neutron bomb. Zhao Qizheng, the chief government 
spokesman, said Chinese scientists developed neutron bombs and 
miniaturized atomic warheads in the 1970s and '80s. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
