<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed higher Monday, with  
technology shares boosted by gains in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	Volume was thin, however, with investors sidelined ahead of the  
U.S. consumer price index, scheduled for release Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 592 European companies rose 1.18  
points, or 0.4 percent, to close at 305.78. The Dow Jones Euro 
Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in countries that joined 
the single currency, closed up 1.27 points at 319.02. 
</P>
<P>
	Among European bourses, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index closed up  
0.7 percent to 5,257.50 as MAN gained 1.45 euros to close at 33.89 
euros, on fresh speculation that the group is eyeing Fiat's Iveco 
and Renault's truck division as potential partners for its 
commercial vehicles operations. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paris CAC-40 index closed up 0.6 percent to 4,458.75, but  
banking stocks came under pressure as the market awaits a final 
decision on the banking takeover battle between Banque National de 
Paris and both Societe Generale and Paribas. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, the FTSE 100 index of blue-chip shares fell 0.2  
percent, to 6,235.4. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 14.11 points to 3724.68,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 14.75 points at 3671.24. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
