<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Astros' Moises Alou Recovery Slowed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Moises Alou might not make it back into the  
Houston Astros' lineup by his target date of Sept. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	The All-Star left fielder has missed the entire season since  
wrecking his left knee in a treadmill accident before spring 
training. He had hoped to join the Astros by the start of next 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's difficult to put a timetable on a severe injury,''  
general manager Gerry Hunsicker said Monday. ``He had set his 
sights on Sept. 1 for a return but now it looks like it will take 
longer.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hunsicker had hoped Alou could go on a rehab assignment in the  
minors before Sept. 1, when the minor league season ends. 
</P>
<P>
	``After Sept. 1, it would be more difficult to get him rehab  
work,'' Hunsicker said. ``We'd have to create some simulated games 
here to try and get him ready.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The two-time NL Central champions are three percentage points  
behind Cincinnati in the division race. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
