<HEADLINE> Blue Jays' Wells To Make Next Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Blue Jays' left-hander David Wells, who was  
scratched from his last start because of a stiff back, will make 
his scheduled start on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Wells missed his last start Friday. He threw on the side Monday  
and said his back was still sore but that he could still pitch. 
</P>
<P>
	Blue Jays' right-hander Joey Hamilton, who has an impingement in  
his right shoulder, also threw on the side and plans to make his 
scheduled start Friday. Hamilton said he expects to pitch with the 
soreness for the rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	He also admitted he pitched tentatively in his last start, when  
he gave up eight runs in just one-third of an inning. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's is scary because you can blow out your arm with one  
pitch,'' Hamilton said. ``I threw as hard as I could in the 
bullpen. I felt it when I threw my slider. It's just something I'm 
going to have to deal with.'' 
  	   	
</P>
