<DOCNO> APW19990816.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 16:40:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Detroit Lions Sign Steve Morrison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIVERSITY CENTER, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Lions on Monday  
signed free agent linebacker Steve Morrison to replace Matt 
Russell, who suffered a season-ending knee injury in Friday's 
exhibition opener at Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	``Morrison gives us immediate help,'' Lions coach Bobby Ross  
said. ``He's actually a little bit bigger than I thought he was. 
We're very fortunate to have someone of that caliber.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Morrison, 6-foot-3 and 246 pounds, was a standout at Brother  
Rice High School and Michigan and played his first four seasons 
with the Indianapolis Colts, seeing action in 58 games. He has 
started 29 games in his pro career, including 12 last season, when 
he had 65 tackles and one sack. 
</P>
<P>
	Getting called up by the Lions was ``a dream come true,''  
Morrison said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I take a lot of pride in the fact that people said I couldn't  
do it, but I'm still around,'' he said after Monday afternoon's 
practice at Saginaw Valley State University, his first workout with 
his new team. 
</P>
<P>
	Morrison was a three-year starter at Michigan, where he had 333  
tackles and six interceptions in his career. As a senior in 1994, 
he led the Wolverines with 122 tackles and was a semifinalist for 
the Butkus Award, given to the best linebacker in college football. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
