<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sosa Homers Off Johnson for No. 47 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Sammy Sosa hit a two-run homer off Randy Johnson  
in the sixth inning Monday night for his 47th home run of the 
season, tying him with Mark McGwire for the major league lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa had struck out in his last five at-bats against Johnson in  
the past week, twice in this game. 
</P>
<P>
	But in the sixth, the Cubs star connected against the Arizona  
ace for a 456-foot shot into the eating area outside Friday's Front 
Row restaurant in the second deck in left field. It was his fourth 
homer in his last three games. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa's 47th homer came in Chicago's 117th game. Last year, he  
also hit No. 47 on Aug. 16, in Chicago's 124th game. 
  	   	
</P>
