<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dodge Gets `Different' Ad Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- ``The New Dodge'' is getting old, so  
the Dodge division of DaimlerChrysler AG is replacing it with a 
different slogan. 
</P>
<P>
	The automaker's new slogan: ``Dodge Different.''  
</P>
<P>
	``Our customers today have told us we're different, different  
than we used to be and different from our competitors,'' said Jim 
Julow, division vice president. ``We're going to wear the 
`different' term like a badge.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The new campaign officially begins Sept. 1 with a series of  
print ads. Television and outdoor advertising will follow 
nationwide Sept. 7, though some billboard ads will be displayed in 
the Detroit area starting this week. 
</P>
<P>
	Dodge says the new tagline will accompany its largest print and  
television campaign in the division's 85-year history. The campaign 
was created by BBDO Worldwide's Southfield office. 
</P>
<P>
	The print ads show no cars, opting instead to make their point  
in simple, graphic terms. One ad, for example, shows six folded 
white dress shirts. Above the ``Dodge Different'' line is a red, 
unfolded Hawaiian print shirt. 
</P>
<P>
	The ``New Dodge'' campaign began in 1992 with the introduction  
of the '93 Intrepid sedan, which marked the start of an overhaul of 
Dodge's model line that previously was dominated by versions of the 
boxy K-cars. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
