<HEADLINE> Son, Dad Drown After Rescue Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TWO RIVERS, Wis. (AP) -- A birthday celebration at a state park  
turned deadly Monday when a young boy and his father drowned in 
Lake Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims were identified as Paul Boersma, 37, and his son  
Zacherie, 9, Manitowoc County Deputy Coroner Bonnie Kretsch said. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims' extended family had gathered at Point Beach State  
Park to celebrate the boy's tenth birthday next week, according to 
sheriff's Inspector Kenneth Petersen. 
</P>
<P>
	``The boy was out swimming in the lake with a couple of his  
cousins. They got in trouble with some undertows. The lake was kind 
of rough (with) 2- to 5-foot waves,'' Petersen said. 
</P>
<P>
	The two cousins made it back to shore and alerted relatives  
about the missing boy. The child's father jumped in the lake to 
rescue his son and was also pulled under by strong undercurrents, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	There was a notice on a chalkboard Monday at the park entrance,  
reading: ``Attn. Swimmers -- Strong Current!'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
