<HEADLINE> Calif. Family Stabbed Before Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTERVILLE, Calif. (AP) -- A man apparently killed his wife and  
two of their daughters before killing himself and their youngest 
child in a house fire, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	All five bodies were found last week in a bedroom of their  
house. They were burned beyond recognition and investigators pieced 
together the slaughter after autopsies were performed. 
</P>
<P>
	Arnulfo Gonzalez, a part-time pizza delivery man who also worked  
for Wal-Mart, apparently repeatedly stabbed his 25-year-old wife, 
Erica, 11-year-old stepdaughter Monica Lopez and 3-year-old 
Jasmine, Police Chief Bud Garman said. 
</P>
<P>
	A flammable liquid was spread through the bedroom, causing an  
explosion that killed Gonzalez and year-old Alejandra. The wife and 
two older daughters were stabbed before the explosion, autopsy 
results showed. 
</P>
<P>
	Police don't know why he did it, police Capt. Silver Rodriguez  
said. Police have no record of domestic violence calls and found no 
evidence suggesting anyone outside the home was involved. 
  	   	
</P>
