<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Falls in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed in European trading  
Monday. Gold fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0567 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0568 Friday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro 
traded at $1.0558. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday,  
included 114.81 Japanese yen, down from 115.92; 1.5153 Swiss 
francs, down from 1.5162; 1.4793 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4773. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6024, down from $1.6048.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 114.75 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6007. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8509 German marks, up from 1.8507; 
6.2076 French francs, up from 6.2070; 2.0855 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0853; 1,832.37 Italian lire, up from 1,832.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold in London was quoted at $258.80 bid per troy ounce, down  
from $260.35 on Friday. In Zurich the bid price was $258.55, down 
from $260.35. Gold fell $1.20 in Hong Kong to $259.35. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver in London was quoted at $5.21 bid per troy ounce, down  
from $5.30. 
  	   	
</P>
