<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Regally Appealing Wins at Saratoga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Regally Appealing trailed the  
leaders into the stretch then closed on the outside for a head 
victory over Miss Wineshine in the $150,000 Grade II Adirondack 
Stakes at Saratoga on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Wineshine, the favorite in the field of six 2-year-old  
fillies, was another 3 3/4 lengths in front of Trump My Heart. 
</P>
<P>
	The scene was set for a closer like Regally Appealing as Trump  
My Heart, Magicalmysterycat and Miss Wineshine vied for the lead 
into the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the second in three career starts for the  
Florida-bred filly by Valid Appeal from the Banner Bob mare, Regal 
Pennant. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Edgar Prado and carrying 114 pounds, Regally Appealing  
covered 6 1/2 furlongs in 1:16:4 and earned $90,000 for Heiligbrodt 
Racing Stable. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $16.40, $5.10 and $4.30. Miss Wineshine paid  
$2.90 and $2.40, while Trump My Heart was $4.50 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
