<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *CKE Restaurants, down 3 15/16 at 9 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company expects to earn 19 cents to 21 cents a share in the  
second quarter. Analysts surveyed by First Call/Thomson Financial 
forecast 33 cents per share. CKE cited lower-than-anticipated 
revenues and operating margins at its Carl's Jr. and Hardee's 
restaurants. 

</P>
<P>
 *Venator Group Inc., up 1 1/8 at 10    	
</P>
<P>
	The former Woolworth will sell or close eight of its non-core  
businesses, totaling more than 500 stores, in an effort to focus 
its business on its sporting goods stores. The company will retain 
businesses including Foot Locker and Champs Sports. 

</P>
<P>
 *Nielsen Media Research Inc., up 4 1/2 at 37 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Dutch publisher VNU will buy Nielsen, the company best known for  
its television ratings, in a deal valued at $2.7 billion. VNU wants 
to use Nielsen to build its business and marketing information 
services. 

</P>
<P>
 *Terra Nova Holdings Ltd., up 5 1/16 at 31  
</P>
<P>
 *Markel Corp., down 8 1/2 at 176 
</P>
<P>
	In a deal that would combine two big specialty insurance  
companies, Markel will acquire Terra Nova for cash and stock valued 
at $905 million. Markel said Terra Nova shareholders can choose 
between cash, stock or a combination for their shares. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Players International Inc., up 1 11/32 at 7 29/32  
</P>
<P>
 *Harrah's Entertainment Inc., up 3/4 at 22 5/8 on the NYSE 
</P>
<P>
	Harrah's made a cash bid of about $272 million for Players, the  
operator of several riverboat casinos. Harrah's said it intends to 
convert each of the Players properties to one of its existing 
brands, Showboat or Harrah's. 

</P>
<P>
 *Fidelity Financial of Ohio Inc., up 6 1/8 at 18 7/16  
</P>
<P>
 *Provident Financial Group Inc., down 2 3/16 at 40 7/16 
</P>
<P>
	Provident will acquire Fidelity Financial in a stock swap valued  
at $191.6 million. Provident will take a $12 million charge for the 
deal, which it said will have a neutral effect on earnings. 

</P>
<P>
 *Emusic.com Inc., up 1 5/16 at 16 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	America Online will offer Emusic.com's dowloadable music through  
its online ICQ, Spinner and Winamp services. The three-year 
agreement calls for Emusic.com to pay AOL a fixed marketing fee and 
a share of transaction revenue. 

</P>
<P>
 *Broadcom Corp., up 7 3/8 at 127 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Broadcom, a chip designer, released a new chip that integrates  
video, computer data and voice technology for corporate networks. 
The company said the chip combines the functions of 10 chips, and 
will sell for less than $100 apiece in bulk quantities. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
