<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Khristich Fets $2.8M From Arbitrator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- An arbitrator ruled Monday that the Boston Bruins  
will have to pay forward Dmitri Khristich $2.8 million, a raise of 
$850,000, if they want to keep him next season. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Bruins elect not to pay Khristich, he will become a free  
agent. 
</P>
<P>
	The 30-year-old left wing from Kiev, Ukraine, scored 29 goals  
and had 41 assists last season. In 12 playoff games, he had three 
goals and four assists. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bruins submitted a figure of $1.95 million to arbitration,  
which is what Khristich made last season, while he asked for $3.5 
million, according to WBZ-AM in Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	Although the Bruins would not discuss what was offered and  
asked, a spokeswoman confirmed the arbitrator's award and said it 
``basically came down in the middle.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The team has 72 hours to make its decision.  
</P>
<P>
	Khristich has scored 225 goals with 282 assists for a total of  
507 points in nine NHL seasons. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
