<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Toys R Us Reports Sales Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARAMUS, N.J. (AP) -- Toys R Us Inc.'s second-quarter earnings  
fell 14 percent compared with the same period a year ago, due to 
costs associated with the development of its Internet subsidiary, 
toysrus.com. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paramus, N.J.-based company reported Monday that it earned  
$12 million, or 5 cents a share, compared with $14 million, or 5 
cents a share, a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	The 1999 results include a $4 million charge to cover costs from  
toysrus.com. Last year's second-quarter results also included a $4 
million charge related to debt extinguishment. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street analysts surveyed by First Call/Thomson Financial  
had expected the company to earn 6 cents a share for the 
three-month period ended July 31. Shares of Toys R Us rose 62 1/2 
cents at $15.81 3/4 in trading on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Second-quarter sales were $2.2 billion, compared to $2 billion  
in the same period a year ago. Sales at stores open at least a 
year, an industry gauge of performance, were up 4 percent in the 
second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Toys R Us has been reorganizing its entire business over the  
past year amid slumping sales and profits. Last year, giant 
discounter Wal-Mart topped Toys R Us as the biggest toy chain in 
the nation. 
</P>
<P>
	Toys R Us has responded by beginning a renovation of its 1,500  
stores, creating a brighter layout that is easier to navigate. The 
company said it remodeled about 80 stores in the second quarter and 
expects to have about 170 stores operating under the new format by 
the upcoming holiday selling season. 
</P>
<P>
	Toys R Us is also stepping up its efforts on the Internet to  
better compete with online rivals Amazon.com and eToys. 
</P>
<P>
	But it has run into some troubles with toysrus.com. Earlier this  
month, Toys R Us named veteran toy industry executive John Barbour 
to head the online unit after University Games founder and CEO 
Robert Moog backed out of the job. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, the company announced Monday that it ended its  
agreement with Benchmark Capital, which said earlier this year that 
it would invest in toysrus.com. Benchmark is a Silicon Valley 
venture capital firm that helped bankroll such Internet successes 
as the online auction house eBay. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are confident that the strategic initiatives we are  
undertaking will strengthen our business for the long term,'' chief 
executive Robert Nakasone said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	For the first half of the year, Toys R Us earned $29 million, or  
12 cents a share, compared with $33 million, or 12 cents a share, a 
year ago. Sales were $4.37 billion, compared with $4.06 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Toys R Us operates 1,472 stores; 705 toy stores in the United  
States, 438 international toy stores, including franchise stores, 
211 Kids R Us children's clothing stores and 118 Babies R Us 
stores. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
