<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-16 15:10:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sacramento Kings Sign Tony Delk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Tony Delk, a backup point guard with  
the Golden State Warriors, signed a multi-year contract with the 
Sacramento Kings on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The team declined to disclose terms of the free agent agreement.  
</P>
<P>
	Delk, 25, has averaged 7.8 points, 1.9 rebounds and 2.1 assists  
in 174 regular-season games in his three years in the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
	He led Kentucky to the 1996 NCAA Championship and was selected  
by the Charlotte Hornets as the 16th pick in the draft that year. 
</P>
<P>
	Delk spent his rookie season with the Hornets and was acquired  
by the Golden State Warriors in a trade early in the 1997-98 
season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
